## Style DNA (80+ Pinterest images analysed)

### Signature look
Grey/taupe long-sleeve button-collar knit polo + black slim trousers + brown leather belt + watch + dark leather shoes or brown sneaker. Most-pinned single outfit across all boards.

### Core aesthetic
"Quiet luxury with sneaker energy" — Southern European smart-casual. Sharp but never stiff. Always one unexpected element (sneakers with a suit, knit instead of shirt, loafers with jeans).

### Layering system
- Level 1 (casual): knit polo or Lacoste polo + slim chinos + white sneakers
- Level 2 (smart casual): crew-neck knit over shirt collar showing + slim trousers + white sneakers or brown loafers
- Level 3 (office): cardigan or V-neck over shirt + slim chinos + brown oxfords OR blazer over knit polo + dark trousers + sneakers
- Level 4 (formal): navy/beige blazer or suit + knitwear/shirt underneath + brown leather shoes

### Colour palette
Tops: navy, grey/taupe, camel/brown, burgundy/wine, forest green, cream/off-white, black
Bottoms: navy, charcoal grey, stone/beige, olive green, mid-wash blue jeans, black
Shoes: cognac/tan brown leather, white leather sneakers, heritage runner colourways
Always: brown leather belt matching shoes, silver or gold watch

### Knitwear preferences (most important category)
- Long-sleeve button-collar knit polo: grey, taupe, cream, navy, black — worn solo or under blazer
- Short-sleeve knit polo: charcoal grey, forest green, olive — smarter casual
- Crew-neck sweater: navy, burgundy, forest green, camel — always over shirt with collar showing
- Cardigan (V-neck or shawl): navy, camel — layered office look
- Quarter-zip: dark green, camel, burgundy — over shirt or tee
- Cable-knit crew: cream/off-white — statement texture piece
- Turtleneck: navy or black — under check/tweed blazer in winter

### Blazers (two lanes)
1. Navy slim blazer — most versatile, worn with everything
2. Beige/camel blazer — casual/summer, with white shirt + olive or navy trousers

### Shoes (four lanes)
1. Brown/cognac cap-toe oxford or full brogue — formal days
2. Brown cognac loafer — smart casual, Italian style
3. Brown leather sneaker with white sole — smart-casual bridge
4. Heritage runner (NB 997/998/1500, Reebok Classic, Adidas Stan Smith/Samba) — leisure

### Fit
Slim through chest and shoulder, tapered leg. Never baggy, never overly tight. Slight break or no break at ankle.

### Key rules
- Brown leather belt always matches shoes in tone
- Watch on wrist in every smart outfit
- Sunglasses outdoors — classic wayfarer or aviator
- Zero large logos — small embroidered logo acceptable (Lacoste croc, RL pony)
- One pattern piece maximum per outfit
- Pocket square when wearing a blazer for formal occasions

